<div class="app-card-container">
  <div class="card px-3 px-md-4 py-3 py-md-4">

    <h1>About Me</h1>

    <hr>

    <div class="card-block">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-12">
          <%= image_tag "profile.jpg", width: 250, alt: "Profile image", class: 'profile-image' %>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-8 col-sm-12"
          <p>I am a junior rails developer with a lot of mettle to become master sooner than later. I have started my codding jurney with creating Wordpress sites. They were quite easy to set up but every modyfication of existing template was a challange. I've leared how painful CSS can be but also how helpful bit of Javascript could be. I am trying to "soak" into coding by surrounding myself with quality coding content all day long. </p>

          <p class="card-block-left">
            <button
              class="btn btn-primary"
              type="button"
              data-toggle="collapse"
              data-target="#jobHistory"
              aria-expanded="false"
              aria-controls="jobHistory"
            >
             Job History
            </button>

            <button
             class="btn btn-primary"
             type="button"
             data-toggle="collapse"
             data-target="#education"
             aria-expanded="false"
             aria-controls="education"
           >
            Education
            </button>
          </p>

           <p>
             <div class="collapse" id="jobHistory">
               <div class="card card-block-left card-job">
                 Job 1
               </div>

               <div class="card card-block-left card-job">
                 Job 2
               </div>
             </div>

             <div class="collapse" id="education">
               <div class="card card-block-left card-job">
                 School 1
               </div>

               <div class="card card-block-left card-job">
                 School 2
               </div>
             </div>
           </p>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
